# devops-exp-1
✅ STEP 1 — Create repo (browser)
Open: https://github.com
Click + → New repository
Name: myproject
Click Create repository

✅ STEP 2 — Open Command Prompt

✅ STEP 3 — Clone repo
git clone https://github.com/santhosh444-ai/myproject.git
cd myproject

✅ STEP 4 — Create first file + commit
echo My DevOps Project > README.md
git add README.md
git commit -m "Initial commit"
git push origin main

✅ STEP 5 — Create feature branch + commit
git checkout -b feature/hello
echo Hello > hello.txt
git add hello.txt
git commit -m "feat: hello"
git push -u origin feature/hello

✅ STEP 6 — Create Pull Request (browser)
Open: https://github.com/santhosh444-ai/myproject
Click Compare & pull request
Click Create pull request

✅ STEP 7 — Merge branch
git checkout main
git merge feature/hello
git push origin main

✅ STEP 8 — Show output
git log --oneline --graph

🔥 FINAL (what you did)
Initialized repo
Committed file
Created branch
Pushed to GitHub
Created PR
Merged branch

